<BaseLayout title="Common LoRA Training Mistakes" description="Avoid common LoRA mistakes such as unclear captions, tiny datasets, duplicates, and overtraining." canonicalPath="/lora/common-mistakes/"><article class="content-section article-body"><h1>Common LoRA Training Mistakes</h1><p>Common mistakes include using too few images, leaving duplicates, writing vague captions, mixing unrelated concepts, and overtraining until the model becomes brittle.</p><p>Test early with neutral prompts and varied scenes. A useful LoRA should respond to the trigger without forcing every output into one narrow pose or background.</p></article></BaseLayout>
